---

import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
const images = import.meta.glob('/src/assets/**/*.{jpeg,jpg,png,gif,webp,svg}', { eager: true });
import '../styles/global.css';
---
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Privacy Policy | CyberBells</title>
    <meta name="description" content="CyberBells Privacy Policy">
    <link rel="icon" type="image/x-icon" href="/favicon.ico">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@300;400;500;600;700;800&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <style>
        .privacy-section {
            padding: 120px 20px 80px;
            background: var(--color-surface, #ffffff);
            min-height: 100vh;
        }
        .privacy-container {
            max-width: 900px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            color: var(--color-ink, #1a1a1a);
            font-family: inherit;
        }
        .privacy-title {
            font-size: 2.5rem;
            font-weight: 700;
            margin-bottom: 2rem;
            color: var(--color-ink);
        }
        .privacy-content {
            line-height: 1.8;
            font-size: 1.1rem;
            color: var(--color-p, #4a4a4a);
        }
        .privacy-content h2 {
            font-size: 1.5rem;
            font-weight: 600;
            margin-top: 2.5rem;
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
            color: var(--color-ink);
        }
        .privacy-content p {
            margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <nav class="navbar">
        <div class="nav-container">
            <a href="/" class="nav-logo" style="text-decoration: none;">
                <Image src={images['/src/assets/Logo/CyberLogo.png']?.default} alt="CyberLogo" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
            </a>
        </div>
    </nav>

    <section class="privacy-section">
        <div class="privacy-container">
            <h1 class="privacy-title">Privacy Policy</h1>
            
            <div class="privacy-content">
                <p>
                  Cyberbells ITES Pvt. Ltd. (“Cyberbells,” “we,” “us,” or “our”) values your privacy and is committed to protecting the personal information you share with us. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your data when you access our website or use our services. We comply with all applicable data protection laws, including the Indian IT Act and other relevant regulations.
                </p>
    
                <h2>1. Consent</h2>
                <p>
                  By using our website and services, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agreed to this Privacy Policy. Continued use of our website constitutes your consent to the practices outlined herein. This policy forms part of our Terms and Conditions.
                </p>
    
                <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
                <p>We may collect the following types of information:</p>
                <p>
                  a. Personal Identification and Contact Information: Name, email address, phone number, postal address.<br />
                  b. Account Information: Usernames, passwords, and other account-related details. <br />
                  c. Payment Information: Credit or debit card details and banking information, which are handled securely via authorized third-party payment service providers. <br />
                  d. Usage Data: IP address, browser type, operating system, pages visited, and other analytics. <br />
                  e. Communication Data: Records of correspondence with us, including emails and chat logs. <br />
                  f. Marketing Preferences: Your preferences for receiving promotional communications. <br />
                  g. Device Information: Details about the device you use to access our services. 
                </p>
    
                <h2>How We Collect Data:</h2>
                <p>
                  Directly from you when you fill forms, create an account, or make transactions. <br />
                  Automatically through cookies and tracking technologies <br />
                  From third-party services integrated with our website, such as payment processors and analytics tools.
                </p>
    
                <h2>3. Purpose of Data Use</h2>
                <p>
                  Your personal information is used to: <br />
                  Process and fulfill orders, payments, and service requests. <br />
                  Offer, operate, and enhance our services as well as improve the overall website experience. <br />
                  Communicate with you about your account, orders, or service updates.<br />
                  Personalize your interactions and provide tailored content. <br />
                  Send marketing and promotional communications (with your consent). <br />
                  Conduct research and analysis to enhance our services. <br />
                  Fulfill statutory and regulatory requirements and respond to valid legal or governmental requests. <br />
                  Maintain website security and prevent fraudulent activities.
                </p>
    
                <h2>4. Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
                <p>
                  We may share your information with: <br />
                  Service Providers: Third-party vendors such as payment processors, shipping partners, and analytics providers who assist in operating our services. <br />
                  Legal Authorities: When required by law or to protect Cyberbells’ rights. <br />
                  Business Transfers: In the event of a merger, restructuring, acquisition, or transfer of ownership or assets of the company. <br />
                  We do not trade, rent, or sell your personal information to any unrelated third parties.
                </p>
    
                <h2>5. Data Protection</h2>
                <p>
                  We apply strong security practices to protect your personal information, including: <br />
                  Applying encryption safeguards to sensitive information during data transmission and while stored on secure systems. <br />
                  Secure storage methods and strict access controls. <br />
                  Regular security audits and vulnerability assessments. <br />
                  Restricting access to personal data strictly to employees and personnel with authorized permissions.
                </p>
    
                <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
                <p>
                  You have specific rights concerning your personal information: <br />
                  Access: You may request confirmation and information regarding the personal data maintained by us. <br />
                  Correction: Update or correct inaccurate information. <br />
                  Deletion: You may request that your personal data be erased, subject to applicable legal or regulatory obligations. <br />
                  Restriction: You may request limitations on how your personal information is processed under specific conditions. <br />
                  Data Portability: Receive your information in a portable format. <br />
                  Objection: You may raise an objection to the use of your personal information for specific purposes, including promotional or marketing activities. <br />
                  Withdraw Consent: Revoke consent previously given. <br />
                  Opt-out: Choose not to receive marketing communications.
                </p>
    
                <h2>7. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
                <p>
                  We use cookies and similar technologies to enhance your browsing experience and collect usage information. Cookie settings can be controlled or modified directly through your web browser preferences.
                </p>
    
                <h2>8. Third-Party Links</h2>
                <p>
                  Our website may include links to third-party websites. Cyberbells is not responsible for their privacy practices. We advise users to carefully read the privacy policies of third-party websites before providing any personal details.
                </p>
    
                <h2>9. Data Retention</h2>
                <p>
                  We retain your personal information only as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this policy, unless a longer retention period is required or permitted by law.
                </p>
    
                <h2>10. Policy Updates</h2>
                <p>
                  Cyberbells reserves the right to revise or update this Privacy Policy periodically. Significant changes will be communicated by posting the updated policy on our website or through other communication channels. We recommend reviewing this policy periodically.
                </p>
    
                <h2>11. Contact Information</h2>
                <p>
                  If you have questions or concerns regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact us via the details provided on our website.
                </p>
    
                <h2>12. Legal Compliance</h2>
                <p>
                  Cyberbells ITES Pvt. Ltd. is committed to complying with all applicable data protection laws and regulations, including the Indian IT Act and related privacy laws.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <footer class="footer-main">
        <div class="footer-container">
            <div class="footer-bottom">
                <p class="copyright">
                    © <span id="currentYear"></span> Cyberbells. All rights reserved.
                </p>
                <a href="https://profiles.dunsregistered.com/DunsRegisteredProfileAnywhere.aspx?key1=3198515&PaArea=Email" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="duns-link">
                    <Image src={images['/src/assets/Logo/cyberbells_footer.jpg']?.default} alt="Cyberbells Duns" class="duns-img" />
                </a>
                <div class="footer-legal">
                    <a href="/privacy-policy" class="privacy-link">Privacy Policy</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </footer>
    <script>
        document.getElementById('currentYear').textContent = new Date().getFullYear();
    </script>
</body>
</html>
